tree.title: svelte-treeview
tree.text:
This is demo of [keenmate/svelte-treeview](https://github.com/keenmate/svelte-treeview) component. View full documentation [here](https://github.com/KeenMate/svelte-treeview/blob/master/README.md). 
You can change properties of Treeview in options tab.
View all events by enabling *show console*.
Tree is saved in your local storage so if something isnt working first try restarting the tree.
You can see all properties of nodes if you enable *showNodes*

This demo is about creating Dota 2 team, where you can have maximum of 5 heroes per team
Dragging teams and categories is disabled,
same as inserting nodes on root level and above/below games.  This is done with **nestDisabled**, **insertDisabled** and **isDraggable**.
Limit of 5 heroes is enforced by **beforeMovedCallback**, that cancels any move that would put more than 5 heores in one team. You can also only place hero into its category or team. This is done with **dragEnterCallback**
